definition.value: Oryza punctata is a grass in the rice genus Oryza, also known as red rice, related to cultivated rice Oryza sativa.

Triticum urartu, also known as red wild einkorn, is a grass species related to wheat, and native to western Asia. It is a diploid species whose genome is the A genome of the allopolyploid hexaploid bread wheat Triticum aestivum, which has genomes AABBDD.

Aegilops speltoides is an edible plant in the Poaceae family native to Southeastern Europe and Western Asia, which is often used for animal feed, and it has grown in cultivated beds. This plant is an important natural source disease resistance in wheat, and it is known or likely to be susceptible to barley mild mosaic bymovirus.
Zea mays subsp. mexicana is one of the two annual diploid species that represents teosinte.

Fungi are eukaryotic organisms that belong to their own kingdom, separate from the other eukaryotic life kingdoms of plants and animals. It includes unicellular microorganisms such as yeasts and molds, as well as multicellular fungi that produce familiar fruiting forms known as mushrooms.
